Dialogue: 10,0:00:32.53,0:00:36.95,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,In August, with the introduction of the block system that subdivided Tokyo into 23 wards,
Dialogue: 10,0:00:36.96,0:00:40.81,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,Yamamoto Shinichi was appointed head of the Katsushika combined block.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:40.81,0:00:44.36,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,Ever since, he has been tirelessly crisscrossing the entire ward,
Dialogue: 10,0:00:44.36,0:00:48.59,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,working to create a model block in Katsushika—\Na downtown district of Tokyo—
Dialogue: 10,0:00:48.59,0:00:52.57,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,brimming with the joy and happiness that faith brings, setting an example
Dialogue: 10,0:00:52.57,0:00:54.53,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,for the rest of the nation.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:05.45,0:01:07.72,Thought,,0,0,0,,It's getting quite late...
Dialogue: 10,0:01:08.32,0:01:09.88,Thought,,0,0,0,,I'm tired.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:10.49,0:01:14.39,Thought,,0,0,0,,But what worries me even more \Nis Sensei's health.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:16.34,0:01:20.71,Thought,,0,0,0,,That look of exhaustion at the headquarters meeting wasn't a matter of course. {/just a trifle}
Dialogue: 10,0:01:20.71,0:01:25.93,Thought,,0,0,0,,Sensei is planning to go to Hiroshima soon, \Nbut it may exact a heavy toll on his health. {/it may be life-threatening}
Dialogue: 10,0:01:39.08,0:01:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei, please cancel your trip \Nto Hiroshima tomorrow.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:43.65,0:01:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I beg you!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:46.77,0:01:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Please take some time off \Nto rest your body.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:51.97,0:01:53.55,Default,,0,0,0,,That is not possible.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:54.68,0:01:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll go. I have to go.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:57.28,0:02:02.37,Default,,0,0,0,,If you push yourself too far, \Nyou'll be risking your health, or even your life.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:02.37,0:02:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Please cancel it.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:04.79,0:02:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,How can I ever do that?!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:06.85,0:02:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:02:08.19,0:02:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You think that's something I could do—isn't that right?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:12.63,0:02:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,But as a Buddha’s emissary, how can I take back a decision I’ve already made?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:18.64,0:02:20.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll go there even if I die.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:20.41,0:02:25.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Shinichi, how can it be wrong \Nit that's what the true faith is about? {probably means "where do you think I'm wrong?" but maybe "How could you not see through that?"}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:27.02,0:02:31.17,Thought,,0,0,0,,Sensei puts his life on the line \Nto go to Hiroshima...
Dialogue: 10,0:02:31.86,0:02:34.95,Default,,0,0,0,,4,000 of our comrades are waiting for me.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:34.95,0:02:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Shinichi, don’t stand in the way \Nof my trip to Hiroshima. {lit: let me go to ...}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:38.14,0:02:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether I die or come back alive, \Nit's all in Buddha's hands.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:46.73,0:02:48.49,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:02:52.02,0:02:53.49,Top,,0,0,0,,Good morning.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:54.02,0:02:55.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, shall we get going?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:57.95,0:02:58.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Dear!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:01.76,0:03:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:03.46,0:03:05.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Izumida-san, this is serious!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:14.27,0:03:15.53,Default,,0,0,0,,S-Sensei!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:15.53,0:03:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Call Shinichi...
Dialogue: 10,0:03:21.10,0:03:26.79,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Following evaluations by two specialists—\NDr. Yabe, Toda’s attending physician,
Dialogue: 10,0:03:26.79,0:03:31.02,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and Dr. Kida, a leading gastroenterologist at the University Hospital—
Dialogue: 10,0:03:31.02,0:03:34.51,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Toda was diagnosed \Nwith advanced cirrhosis of the liver.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:35.07,0:03:37.26,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He was ordered to rest in bed
Dialogue: 10,0:03:37.26,0:03:43.02,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and placed on a regimen of medication and a restricted diet as part of his home treatment.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:47.60,0:03:50.79,Thought,,0,0,0,,If we were to lose Sensei now,
Dialogue: 10,0:03:50.79,0:03:54.13,Thought,,0,0,0,,the Common Path would surely crumble.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:54.13,0:03:56.76,Thought,,0,0,0,,How can we let Sensei die?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:56.76,0:04:01.65,Narrator,,0,0,0,,As December went on, \NToda began to show signs of improvement
Dialogue: 10,0:04:01.65,0:04:04.72,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and steadily regained his strength.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:07.46,0:04:10.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Chairman! The tally is in—
Dialogue: 10,0:04:10.09,0:04:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,by the end of this month, Soka Gakkai has confidently exceeded 750,000 households,
Dialogue: 10,0:04:14.63,0:04:17.45,Default,,0,0,0,,reaching 765,000!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:17.45,0:04:19.58,Default,,0,0,0,,That's it! We've done it at last!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:19.58,0:04:22.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Harayama-san, please report \Nto President Toda at once.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:24.89,0:04:28.37,Thought,,0,0,0,,So we've finally reached \Nthe 750,000 households mark?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:28.37,0:04:32.41,Thought,,0,0,0,,We had no more than 3,000 members \Nwhen I made that promise.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:32.87,0:04:38.47,Thought,,0,0,0,,In just six years and seven months, \Nmy most cherished dream was realized.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:38.93,0:04:43.30,Thought,,0,0,0,,It's all thanks to our comrades \Nwho stood by me through thick and thin. {/shared with me the good and bad times }
Dialogue: 10,0:04:43.30,0:04:47.32,Thought,,0,0,0,,The challenge now is making our members \Nin all 750,000 households truly happy.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:47.65,0:04:49.29,Thought,,0,0,0,,More precisely, the question is:
Dialogue: 10,0:04:49.29,0:04:54.29,Thought,,0,0,0,,"What path should we take to guide people \Ntoward happy and fulfilling lives?"
Dialogue: 10,0:05:00.97,0:05:03.71,Thought,,0,0,0,,With faith at its foundation...
Dialogue: 10,0:05:03.71,0:05:10.21,Thought,,0,0,0,,Everything hinges on their ability to stoically persevere in faith, no matter where it leads them.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:10.67,0:05:14.58,Thought,,0,0,0,,What greater goal must I set for them \Nto make it a reality? {lit: for that, what do I need to appeal to (reason, emotions, etc.); to work on (one's emotions); to play on (one's sympathies)​?}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:14.81,0:05:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:05:18.44,0:05:22.11,Thought,,0,0,0,,How should one practice their faith?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:22.11,0:05:24.39,Thought,,0,0,0,,To have faith—what for?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:24.39,0:05:28.89,Thought,,0,0,0,,It's crucial to clearly point out those \Nsignposts for everyone to follow right now.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:30.90,0:05:33.28,Thought,,0,0,0,,All right, it's decided.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:36.65,0:05:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The total number of households \Nconverted in December is 25,089.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:41.13,0:05:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,This allowed us to confidently surpass \Nthe 750,000 households target!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:46.03,0:05:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,At long last, the lifelong goal President Toda \Nset when he took office has been fulfilled!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:55.84,0:05:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The news reinvigorated Toda-sense greatly.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:59.28,0:06:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,On that occasion, \Nhe wanted to reassure everyone
Dialogue: 10,0:06:01.70,0:06:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that he would attend the first service of the year at the headquarters.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:09.66,0:06:13.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Furthermore, as we embark \Non a new journey in the coming year,
Dialogue: 10,0:06:13.33,0:06:14.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei wanted to pass to you
Dialogue: 10,0:06:14.83,0:06:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the "Three Guidelines of Soka Gakkai" \Nas signposts for your faith.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:17.88,0:06:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,As per his request, \NI will now announce them to everyone.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:31.29,0:06:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,These are the three guidelines.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:33.23,0:06:37.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's all work hard next year \Nfor the fulfillment of those.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:39.44,0:06:43.88,Thought,,0,0,0,,These guidelines are filled with Sensei's wish for the happiness of all members.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:43.88,0:06:48.72,Thought,,0,0,0,,Let us engrave them in our hearts \Nas the guidelines for all eternity!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:51.70,0:06:58.65,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The New Year's Service, \Nwhich marked the start of activities for 1958,
Dialogue: 10,0:06:58.65,0:07:02.70,Narrator,,0,0,0,,was held at the Soka Gakkai Headquarters on January 1st.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:12.50,0:07:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei presented us with a New Year poem. \NAllow me to read it now.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:30.41,0:07:31.99,Top,,0,0,0,,That's the current situation.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:31.99,0:07:32.89,Top,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:32.89,0:07:34.40,Top,,0,0,0,,Good job out there.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:34.85,0:07:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, our position in Kansai \Nis pretty much ideal.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:37.85,0:07:42.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It is no exaggeration to say we've laid a firm foundation for the Common Path in Japan.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:44.63,0:07:48.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The real challenge only begins now.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:48.59,0:07:51.16,Default,,0,0,0,,How far will we make it \Nin the next seven years?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:53.10,0:07:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to hurry, Shinichi.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:55.73,0:07:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think we can reach 3 million households in the next seven years?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:59.00,0:08:03.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, we can. \NI will make sure we do.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:03.15,0:08:05.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I am your faithful disciple.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:05.24,0:08:09.22,Default,,0,0,0,,As a disciple, it's my duty \Nto fulfill my master's vision.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:09.86,0:08:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Rest assured.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:11.18,0:08:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Good. I look forward to seeing how far \Nyou can take it with your own hands.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:16.91,0:08:21.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't it be wonderful if the time had come when our ranks numbered 10 million believers?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:21.88,0:08:25.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I'm looking forward to it. I really do.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:25.48,0:08:30.12,Thought,,0,0,0,,As part of his will, sensei left me \Nmore goals for the future.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:30.12,0:08:34.14,Thought,,0,0,0,,I absolutely must achieve them \Nand make him happy.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:37.02,0:08:41.00,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,On March 1st, a pompous dedication ceremony
Dialogue: 10,0:08:41.00,0:08:44.21,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,and a special commemorative service were held
Dialogue: 10,0:08:44.21,0:08:49.02,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,at the newly built Grand Auditorium \Nof Honmon Branch amid joyous crowds. {法華本門大講堂 - can't really find it mentioned anywhere else so no idea what to call it}
Dialogue: 10,0:08:49.02,0:08:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Let us all celebrate together the completion
Dialogue: 10,0:08:53.97,0:08:59.85,Default,,0,0,0,,of this magnificent Grand Auditorium,\Nmade possible by the heartfelt contributions
Dialogue: 10,0:08:59.85,0:09:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,of over 750,000 Soka Gakkai households!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:11.82,0:09:16.66,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The mountain hikes in celebration of the Grand Auditorium's completion began on the 2nd, {think I called them "mountaineering trips/mountain-climbing expeditions" or something previously}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:16.66,0:09:18.92,Narrator,,0,0,0,,with 200,000 people \Nbooking a climb that month. {think she means "that month, it was planned for 200000 pilgrims to climb it"}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:19.31,0:09:24.41,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,The combined number of participants in the overnight and day trips reached 7,000 each day,
Dialogue: 10,0:09:24.41,0:09:28.93,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,making Taisekiji Temple \Nmore vibrant than ever before. {/bustling with people throughout the day}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:33.70,0:09:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Shinichi, my friend, Prime Minister Mine, {refers to https://ja.wikipedia.org/wiki/%E5%B2%B8%E4%BF%A1%E4%BB%8B#:~:text=191%5D%E3%80%82-,%E5%89%B5%E4%BE%A1%E5%AD%A6%E4%BC%9A%E7%AC%AC2%E4%BB%A3%E4%BC%9A%E9%95%B7%E3%83%BB%E6%88%B8%E7%94%B0%E5%9F%8E%E8%81%96%E3%81%A8,%E5%8D%97%E6%9D%A1%E5%BE%B3%E7%94%B7%E3%83%BB%E5%89%8D%E5%BB%BA%E8%A8%AD%E5%A4%A7%E8%87%A3%E3%82%92%E5%87%BA%E5%B8%AD%E3%81%95%E3%81%9B%E3%81%9F%E3%80%82,-%E3%83%8E%E3%83%BC%E3%83%99%E3%83%AB%E5%B9%B3%E5%92%8C%E8%B3%9E ; check TL notes}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:37.18,0:09:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,called me and said he'd like to visit \Non Sunday, March 16th.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:42.21,0:09:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:43.79,0:09:48.59,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a good opportunity. \NLet's send the youth division climbing that day.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:48.59,0:09:54.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And let's also hold a rehearsal, a mock exam ceremony for the future of the Common Path. {そして将来のために 広宣流布の模擬試験予行演習となる式典をしよう ; no idea what he means}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:54.68,0:09:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:55.50,0:10:00.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Shinichi, during this ritual ceremony \Non March 16th,
Dialogue: 10,0:10:00.10,0:10:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to entrust the official seal \Nof the Common Path to you. {(ribbon of) an official seal}{kimitachi so "you guys" but I think it doesn't matter}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:04.46,0:10:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:10:05.63,0:10:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ll be in overall charge of this ceremony.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:09.19,0:10:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't hold back and give it your best.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:11.94,0:10:16.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Yessir, I’ll make it a perfect gathering for giving my oath as the successor of the Common Path. {literal}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:20.29,0:10:22.98,Thought,,0,0,0,,Sensei's waning strength is what worries me.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:22.98,0:10:26.28,Thought,,0,0,0,,Even just walking is getting harder \Nfor him with each passing day.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:26.89,0:10:29.98,Thought,,0,0,0,,What can I do to reduce \Nthe burden on his health?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:31.26,0:10:34.53,Thought,,0,0,0,,Yes, let's prepare a litter. {/palanquin; 車駕}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:46.73,0:10:48.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Good night! {not really morning}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:48.11,0:10:50.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Good job getting here. \NPlease watch your step!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:03.02,0:11:04.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It's good! {guess}
Dialogue: 10,0:11:04.54,0:11:06.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So warm!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:07.15,0:11:11.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I finally get why they told us \Nto bring our own chopsticks and bowls.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:11.86,0:11:17.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true. You can feel Sensei's soul \Nin this pork soup he treated us to. {lit: made with his soul and body but I don't support toda cooked it himself}
Dialogue: 10,0:11:17.14,0:11:20.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And in this cold, \Nit warms you from the inside!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:20.35,0:11:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,That sure is great!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:31.92,0:11:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Mine-san? What Mine-san?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:34.96,0:11:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Y-Yes I'll pass it to him at once.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:37.28,0:11:38.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei, a call for you.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:38.89,0:11:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:11:40.85,0:11:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Toda listening...
Dialogue: 10,0:11:42.24,0:11:45.64,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The caller was Prime Minister Mine.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:45.64,0:11:51.72,Narrator,,0,0,0,,"A diplomatic issue has emerged in the government, and I must address it urgently,
Dialogue: 10,0:11:51.72,0:11:56.49,Narrator,,0,0,0,,so I won't be able to attend the ceremony," he said.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:56.49,0:12:02.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Mine-san, 6,000 of our young members have been waiting quite some time for your arrival.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:02.97,0:12:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't that be unfair towards them? {lit: aren't you tricking/deceiving them}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:08.59,0:12:13.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't need to apologize to me. \NApologize to our young people!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:13.98,0:12:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:16.15,0:12:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,He hung up.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:19.24,0:12:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Prime Minister Mine isn't coming.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:21.12,0:12:21.89,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:12:22.53,0:12:27.21,Thought,,0,0,0,,How would our young men feel when they hear that the Prime Minister won't attend?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:27.21,0:12:29.20,Thought,,0,0,0,,They'll all be depressed.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:29.65,0:12:33.52,Thought,,0,0,0,,All right, let's convene an emergency meeting \Nof the Youth Division leaders.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:34.84,0:12:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Long story short, \NPrime Minister Mine couldn't make it.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:37.89,0:12:38.61,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:12:38.61,0:12:41.39,Default,,0,0,0,,His family and a House of Representatives member Saijo,
Dialogue: 10,0:12:41.39,0:12:46.33,Default,,0,0,0,,who also attended the memorial service on the 1st, will be climbing the mountain on his behalf. {unsure, maybe it's saijo's family}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:48.22,0:12:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,With or without the Prime Minister,
Dialogue: 10,0:12:50.73,0:12:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,let's carry out the ceremony in full force as planned and give the youth a rousing welcome. {actually "to the group" but idk who he refers to}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:57.48,0:12:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:58.42,0:13:01.43,Default,,0,0,0,,This doesn't change that today's ceremony
Dialogue: 10,0:13:01.43,0:13:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,would be a mock ceremony \Nfor when the Common Path is achieved. {lit: to commemorate KP - no idea what he means}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:05.03,0:13:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I regard everyone here today as my successor, {lit: all participants}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:07.76,0:13:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and through this ceremony, I will entrust you with the cause of the Common Path.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:14.13,0:13:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Since the PM isn't coming, I intend to encourage everyone with my own strength.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:18.76,0:13:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:24.62,0:13:28.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It's too big and unfit for a real battle. \NYou can't do any fighting in this.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:28.95,0:13:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:13:30.08,0:13:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:13:31.96,0:13:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei, please forgive me for this oversight.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:37.82,0:13:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,However, your disciples \Nput their souls into this litter.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:42.32,0:13:44.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, let us use it. {/ride it}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:47.20,0:13:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Very well.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:49.52,0:13:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Toda-sensei!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:49.98,0:13:51.41,Overlap,,0,0,0,,Toda-sensei!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:52.83,0:13:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:13:58.23,0:14:03.87,Thought,,0,0,0,,You’ve all grown up so much—\Ntruly, it’s incredible to see how far you’ve come.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:04.74,0:14:10.04,Thought,,0,0,0,,This could well be the last time \Nwe all get to gather like this…
Dialogue: 10,0:14:14.58,0:14:17.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, it's Sensei!  \NToda-sensei!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:17.54,0:14:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei! How are you?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:20.17,0:14:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei! Please stay well forever! {in good health; healthy; well; fit; robust; strong}
Dialogue: 10,0:14:24.12,0:14:27.97,Thought,,0,0,0,,The future belongs to the young. {lit: it's the young men who have the power to open up the future}
Dialogue: 10,0:14:28.64,0:14:30.57,Thought,,0,0,0,,As long as we have these young men,
Dialogue: 10,0:14:31.50,0:14:37.02,Thought,,0,0,0,,I have no doubt that we can turn Japan \Ninto the paradise of peace.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:48.74,0:14:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,An address by Toda Josei-sensei!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:51.93,0:14:56.08,Narrator,,0,0,0,,During the ceremony, \NToda spoke from his chair.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:56.56,0:15:01.09,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He tried to stand up and speak, \Nbut was no longer strong enough for that.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:01.09,0:15:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s our mission to carry the Common Path \Nto every corner of the world.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:06.80,0:15:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And today, I pass that noble cause \Nto you, the young men and women.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:12.08,0:15:14.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I entrust its future to you.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:14.39,0:15:16.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Please take good care of the Common Path!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:16.81,0:15:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:15:18.72,0:15:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:15:23.07,0:15:26.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Soka Gakkai is the king of the religious world. {literal; I tried to give this a less overbearing spin, but I couldn't}
Dialogue: 10,0:15:27.14,0:15:29.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You have nothing to fear.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:29.65,0:15:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Never forget your responsibility—\Nyou were chosen to succeed me in this battle,
Dialogue: 10,0:15:34.62,0:15:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the spiritual battle for the Common Path \Nas the young, rising warriors. {lit: warriors of flowers - idk}
Dialogue: 10,0:15:39.20,0:15:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So fight it with courage to the end.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:42.02,0:15:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:43.03,0:15:46.60,Narrator,,0,0,0,,"Soka Gakkai is the king of the religious world."
Dialogue: 10,0:15:46.95,0:15:51.38,Narrator,,0,0,0,,These words stood as a powerful declaration of victory for the Common Path—
Dialogue: 10,0:15:51.38,0:15:53.56,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Toda’s lifelong aspiration.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:53.95,0:16:00.36,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It would also prove to be Toda’s final lion’s roar to the youth. {of his life}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:02.88,0:16:04.80,Thought,,0,0,0,,This is the end...
Dialogue: 10,0:16:04.80,0:16:09.28,Thought,,0,0,0,,Makiguchi-sensei, I have inherited your will \Nand built the solid foundation
Dialogue: 10,0:16:09.28,0:16:11.86,Thought,,0,0,0,,for the Common Path for all eternity.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:12.56,0:16:16.83,Thought,,0,0,0,,And just now, I have also bequeathed \Nits future to my beloved disciples.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:16.83,0:16:24.76,Thought,,0,0,0,,Your aspirations still pulsate \Nin the hearts of the young, redder than blood.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:25.69,0:16:30.22,Thought,,0,0,0,,My work here is done.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:30.22,0:16:33.57,Thought,,0,0,0,,Sensei, did I do well?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:39.85,0:16:45.25,Thought,,0,0,0,,Sensei, you can count on us, your disciples, \Nto carry the torch of the Common Path!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:45.25,0:16:46.99,Thought,,0,0,0,,Leave all worries behind.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:46.99,0:16:52.56,Narrator,,0,0,0,,March 16th would later be commemorated as the Memorial Day of the Common Path—
Dialogue: 10,0:16:52.56,0:16:57.77,Narrator,,0,0,0,,the day Toda's disciples inherited it and vowed \Ntheir renewed commitment to its cause.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:57.77,0:17:02.88,Narrator,,0,0,0,,From March 16th onward, \NToda's health began to deteriorate rapidly. {/fade}
Dialogue: 10,0:17:03.62,0:17:07.34,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Though he was too ill \Nto even rise from his futon unaided,
Dialogue: 10,0:17:07.34,0:17:10.01,Narrator,,0,0,0,,his spirit remained steadfast.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:10.01,0:17:11.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:11.95,0:17:12.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:13.41,0:17:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Shinichi, I dreamed I went to Mexico yesterday.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:19.21,0:17:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Mexico?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:23.85,0:17:26.35,Default,,0,0,0,,They were waiting. \NEveryone was waiting for me.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:26.92,0:17:30.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The people there were yearning \Nfor Nichiren's Buddhism.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:31.55,0:17:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish I could go there, launch the journey of Common Path throughout the world...
Dialogue: 10,0:17:36.14,0:17:37.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei...
Dialogue: 10,0:17:38.58,0:17:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Shinichi, your goal is the world. {/enemy/opponent - not really sure what he means, maybe "you should act against [the background of] the world"}
Dialogue: 10,0:17:42.25,0:17:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Your real stage is the world—\Nbut what a vast stage it is...
Dialogue: 10,0:17:47.11,0:17:49.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Different races, different ethnicities...
Dialogue: 10,0:17:50.40,0:17:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Liberal countries \Nand socialist countries...
Dialogue: 10,0:17:54.07,0:17:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Each country has its own \Napproach to religion.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:56.72,0:17:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Some allow missionary work,
Dialogue: 10,0:17:59.90,0:18:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,while others do not.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:02.12,0:18:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you harmonize the Mystic Law \Nwith all those diverse nations? {/spread lotus sutra to}
Dialogue: 10,0:18:06.19,0:18:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I want you to consider it carefully right now.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:09.03,0:18:14.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The true essence of Buddhism lies in bringing happiness and peace to all humanity.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:17.93,0:18:19.16,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:18:21.37,0:18:22.73,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:18:25.57,0:18:26.33,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:18:29.44,0:18:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Your weak health is what worries me.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:34.97,0:18:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Shinichi, live! \NYou must live a long life and go to the world. {a great deal; very much; a lot​ - maybe "live for great things"}
Dialogue: 10,0:18:42.23,0:18:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I will!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:46.96,0:18:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:18:55.91,0:18:58.58,Top,,0,0,0,,Sensei, good morning.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:59.01,0:19:00.84,Default,,0,0,0,,How are you feeling today?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:00.84,0:19:02.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh... I'm fine.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:02.53,0:19:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Is the mountain pilgrimage proceeding as planned? {/climbing}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:05.94,0:19:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, we have everything under control.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:08.94,0:19:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The pilgrimage will continue for two more days.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:11.38,0:19:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,There haven't been any incidents. \NYou have nothing to worry about.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:14.74,0:19:17.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. So it's all going smoothly?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:18.12,0:19:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Is everyone from our youth well?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:20.31,0:19:23.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, they're all well and doing their best.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:23.70,0:19:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The only possible issue had been \Nthis particularly unruly monk. {https://jisho.org/search/%E9%9D%9E%E9%81%93}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:28.50,0:19:32.33,Default,,0,0,0,,We wanted him to reflect on his actions, \Nso we filed a protest.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:32.76,0:19:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Did anything come out of that? {actually "what does that mean" but need to justify "yes" in the next line}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:34.57,0:19:35.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:36.34,0:19:37.47,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:19:38.03,0:19:45.00,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Shinichi told Toda in detail about the atrocities \Ncommitted by one of the head monks. {所化頭である僧侶 - actually no idea what to make of his post}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:45.52,0:19:49.90,Narrator,,0,0,0,,One of them had been drinking at the inn since morning,
Dialogue: 10,0:19:49.90,0:19:51.84,Narrator,,0,0,0,,despite the ban on alcohol
Dialogue: 10,0:19:51.84,0:19:57.43,Narrator,,0,0,0,,during the Grand Auditorium opening ceremony for security reasons.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:57.43,0:20:02.95,Narrator,,0,0,0,,On another occasion, still drunk, \Nhe verbally abused the young monks,
Dialogue: 10,0:20:02.95,0:20:06.12,Narrator,,0,0,0,,insultingly telling them to go to Mount Minobu.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:06.12,0:20:16.70,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He also placed bells on their heads \Nand struck them unsparingly with the bell sticks.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:16.70,0:20:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, this head monk has long held a grudge against Soka Gakkai and you personally,
Dialogue: 10,0:20:23.10,0:20:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and has been slandering us for some time.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:25.78,0:20:30.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So I thought we should arrange \Na proper meeting and have a thorough discussion.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:31.11,0:20:33.38,Default,,0,0,0,,What a sorry sight... {/how pathetic}
Dialogue: 10,0:20:33.98,0:20:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Shinichi, this might look like a minor dispute,
Dialogue: 10,0:20:37.36,0:20:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,but it actually signals a deeper issue \Nof corruption and decay within the sect.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:43.03,0:20:46.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do monks start to fall \Ninto corruption and depravity?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:47.64,0:20:53.54,Default,,0,0,0,,That's because they've lost sight of living \Nfor the higher purpose of the Common Path.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:53.54,0:20:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,If this one point goes wrong, \Neverything goes wrong.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:58.42,0:21:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It's sad that many monks today,
Dialogue: 10,0:21:00.55,0:21:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,while paying lip service to {\i1}Upholding the Monastic Laws{\i0} just to protect themselves, {令法久住 - I actually don't fucking know what to make of it; lit: order method long time live}
Dialogue: 10,0:21:06.64,0:21:10.29,Default,,0,0,0,,are in no hurry to let go of their selfish earthly desires.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:10.29,0:21:15.71,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, they've become slaves to those desires and sunk to the level of animals. {chikusho = person reborn into the animal realm}
Dialogue: 10,0:21:15.71,0:21:17.72,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:21:20.43,0:21:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like it did during the war, the sect may again harbor demons in the future— {demon of the sixth heaven in the realm of desire who tries to prevent people from doing good​}
Dialogue: 10,0:21:26.62,0:21:31.61,Default,,0,0,0,,those who aim to destabilize the true Dharma \Nand block the Common Path.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:32.27,0:21:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,However, we must never allow \NDaishonin's Buddhism to be ruined!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:38.57,0:21:43.05,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s why you must stand firm \Nand fight the evil festering within the sect—
Dialogue: 10,0:21:43.05,0:21:44.45,Default,,0,0,0,,do you understand, Shinichi?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:45.05,0:21:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:46.76,0:21:48.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Not a step back, remember?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:48.89,0:21:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:49.85,0:21:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't let up on the chase. {literal, could go more readable "never let this evil take root"}
Dialogue: 10,0:21:51.96,0:21:55.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! I will never forget your wise guidance!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:07.51,0:22:10.33,Thought,,0,0,0,,Sensei, please rest assured.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:10.33,0:22:14.48,Thought,,0,0,0,,No matter what happens, \Nwe'll protect Soka Gakkai with our lives!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:15.00,0:22:17.95,Thought,,0,0,0,,Don't let up on the chase!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:19.90,0:22:23.93,Default,,0,0,0,,If this continues, \NSensei is only going to get worse.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:23.93,0:22:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to take him to his home in Tokyo \Nas soon as possible and get him a proper doctor.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:28.79,0:22:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if you’re thinking of moving him to Tokyo, \NI’m not sure it’s even possible...
Dialogue: 10,0:22:33.39,0:22:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,How about having Dr. Kida come here \Nand examine Sensei
Dialogue: 10,0:22:37.65,0:22:40.58,Default,,0,0,0,,so that we can decide on a course of action?
Dialogue: 10,0:22:55.96,0:22:59.21,Thought,,0,0,0,,He still has a steady and strong heartbeat.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:59.21,0:23:02.80,Thought,,0,0,0,,They say his strength has been waning rapidly these past few days.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:02.80,0:23:08.03,Thought,,0,0,0,,In that case, we might need \Nto move him to Tokyo as soon as possible...
Dialogue: 10,0:23:16.00,0:23:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei, we need to leave.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:19.55,0:23:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be accompanying you.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:22.86,0:23:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:23:52.57,0:23:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei, you're safe now.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:55.98,0:23:57.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 10,0:24:07.86,0:24:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Well then, I will now begin working on the treatment. { with all my might}
Dialogue: 10,0:24:11.74,0:24:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Please spare no effort \Nto get the best treatment for Sensei.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:16.00,0:24:19.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Yamamoto-san, thank you \Nfor looking after him so much.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:19.85,0:24:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's nothing.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:22.38,0:24:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll excuse myself for now, \Nbut if anything comes up,
Dialogue: 10,0:24:26.19,0:24:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,don’t hesitate to call me \Nat work or at home.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:29.27,0:24:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:41.13,0:24:45.82,Thought,,0,0,0,,All I can do now is pray \Nfor Sensei's complete recovery.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:45.82,0:24:49.09,Thought,,0,0,0,,I will ask everyone \Nin the youth division to do the same.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:51.85,0:24:55.72,Narrator,,0,0,0,,On April 2nd at 5 p.m., a joint meeting between the board of directors
Dialogue: 10,0:24:55.72,0:25:00.72,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and the youth division leaders \Nwas held at the Soka Gakkai headquarters.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:00.72,0:25:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The agenda for tomorrow's \NHQ Executive Meeting has just been set.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:05.34,0:25:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The exam preparations are also in order, right? {lit: this is also good for academic/educational exam-related matters, right - means they'll be holding the exam, not passing it}
Dialogue: 10,0:25:07.61,0:25:08.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:07.92,0:25:08.49,Overlap,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 10,0:25:10.16,0:25:13.97,Default,,0,0,0,,That should be all for today's meeting...
Dialogue: 10,0:25:15.60,0:25:16.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 10,0:25:17.22,0:25:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Chief Yamamoto, we just got a call from the hospital—it was Sensei’s son, Kyoichi-san.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:23.52,0:25:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,C-Coming!
Dialogue: 10,0:25:27.01,0:25:28.97,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:25:29.49,0:25:30.93,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:25:33.53,0:25:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry for the wait, Yamamoto's here.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:36.73,0:25:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,My father just passed away.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:41.57,0:25:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,He passed away...?
Dialogue: 10,0:25:44.88,0:25:48.11,Default,,0,0,0,,But he was well just this morning...
Dialogue: 10,0:25:48.55,0:25:51.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. It seemed like he was fine.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:51.43,0:25:55.81,Default,,0,0,0,,But at 6:30 p.m., shortly after the doctor \Nhad finished his examination,
Dialogue: 10,0:25:55.81,0:26:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,he passed away peacefully in his sleep, \Nwith my mother by his side...
Dialogue: 10,0:26:00.93,0:26:06.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much to all of you \Nfor taking such good care of him.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:12.60,0:26:16.06,Thought,,0,0,0,,Sensei is no more...
Dialogue: 10,0:26:22.27,0:26:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei had...
Dialogue: 10,0:26:24.88,0:26:27.97,Default,,0,0,0,,passed away just now,
Dialogue: 10,0:26:28.55,0:26:29.73,Default,,0,0,0,,at 6:30.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:29.73,0:26:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:26:30.67,0:26:32.49,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:26:32.49,0:26:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:26:42.96,0:26:50.67,Thought,,0,0,0,,As he had foretold, he departed this world \Njust as the cherry blossoms came into bloom.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:51.78,0:26:57.10,Thought,,0,0,0,,Just as he had planted the saplings \Nof the Mystic Law in over 750,000 families
Dialogue: 10,0:26:57.10,0:26:59.64,Thought,,0,0,0,,and the flowers of happiness had begun to bloom,
Dialogue: 10,0:26:59.64,0:27:05.54,Thought,,0,0,0,,{\fade(0,1000)}he was swept away in an instant—\Nlike the fleeting cherry blossoms. {/scattered away in a flash/disappeared all at once}
Dialogue: 10,0:27:05.96,0:27:12.57,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Toda Josei, who dedicated his life to the Common Path, has now passed into eternal sleep.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:13.19,0:27:19.46,Narrator,,0,0,0,,However, as Toda demonstrated through his own example, the path of a great human revolution—
Dialogue: 10,0:27:19.46,0:27:25.34,Narrator,,0,0,0,,beginning within one person—holds the power \Nto ultimately decide the nation's fate
Dialogue: 10,0:27:25.34,0:27:28.25,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and even remold the fate of the human race.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:28.25,0:27:36.22,Narrator,,0,0,0,,That was the greatest and finest legacy \Nthat Toda Josei left to mankind.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:53.04,0:27:57.74,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:28:00.20,0:28:01.62,Thought,,0,0,0,,Sensei....
Dialogue: 10,0:28:02.81,0:28:05.33,Top,,0,0,0,,How old are you, Yamamoto-kun? {ep2 21:28}
Dialogue: 10,0:28:05.79,0:28:07.21,Top,,0,0,0,,I'm 19 years old.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:07.81,0:28:10.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm. Almost 20, yes? {not in ep2}
Dialogue: 10,0:28:12.19,0:28:13.32,Top,,0,0,0,,Sensei... {ep5 26:09}
Dialogue: 10,0:28:13.86,0:28:14.34,Top,,0,0,0,,Please.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:15.44,0:28:18.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! What do we have here?
Dialogue: 10,0:28:18.10,0:28:22.70,Default,,0,0,0,,"Still serving an old and mystic fate,
Dialogue: 10,0:28:22.68,0:28:26.23,Thought,,0,0,0,,{\pos(350,460)}Though others change, I alter not.”
Dialogue: 10,0:28:26.23,0:28:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, I’ll write you a poem too.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:31.92,0:28:37.63,Default,,0,0,0,,"Whenever I stand on the fields of war,
Dialogue: 10,0:28:38.58,0:28:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Unfailing at my side,\NYou are my sword.”
Dialogue: 10,0:28:43.87,0:28:46.37,Top,,0,0,0,,Shinichi, don't you die. {ep18 28:53}
Dialogue: 10,0:28:46.75,0:28:48.33,Top,,0,0,0,,You {\i1}cannot{\i0} die!
Dialogue: 10,0:28:48.76,0:28:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Shinichi, if ever...
Dialogue: 10,0:28:51.05,0:28:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If you were ever to die, \NI’d rush over to your side,
Dialogue: 10,0:28:56.00,0:28:59.24,Default,,0,0,0,,throw myself over you{ face down}, \Nand die with you then and there!
Dialogue: 10,0:29:00.45,0:29:02.32,Top,,0,0,0,,Sensei, this way.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:08.16,0:29:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, my job here is done.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:12.65,0:29:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I'm prepared to die anytime.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:17.06,0:29:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Shinichi,
Dialogue: 10,0:29:18.67,0:29:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,the rest is up to you.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:22.56,0:29:24.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Please...
Dialogue: 10,0:29:24.46,0:29:25.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course!
Dialogue: 10,0:29:29.94,0:29:32.65,Thought,,0,0,0,,I made a promise to the Sensei.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:33.23,0:29:35.26,Thought,,0,0,0,,I must stand tall now.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:35.96,0:29:40.72,Thought,,0,0,0,,It is my duty to encourage \Nour many grieving comrades!
Dialogue: 10,0:29:41.57,0:29:44.13,Thought,,0,0,0,,Stand up! Rise!
Dialogue: 10,0:29:44.70,0:29:48.41,Thought,,0,0,0,,Become a strong person \Nwho can overcome anything!
Dialogue: 10,0:30:14.83,0:30:20.82,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,News of Toda’s death quickly spread nationwide through newspapers and radio,
Dialogue: 10,0:30:20.82,0:30:25.52,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,and the media swiftly reported remarks from religious scholars and critics
Dialogue: 10,0:30:25.52,0:30:29.85,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,predicting that, without its supreme leader, Soka Gakkai
Dialogue: 10,0:30:29.85,0:30:33.49,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,would descend into internal strife \Nand eventually collapse.
Dialogue: 10,0:30:33.92,0:30:39.05,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And most of the Japanese people \Nneeded no further persuasion.
Dialogue: 10,0:30:39.94,0:30:43.98,Narrator,,0,0,0,,However, Soka Gakkai didn't so much as waver.
Dialogue: 10,0:30:44.47,0:30:49.32,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,With Shinichi Yamamoto—Toda’s most devoted disciple who carried on his legacy in the struggle—
Dialogue: 10,0:30:49.32,0:30:52.48,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,rising as the spiritual cornerstone of the Common Path,
Dialogue: 10,0:30:52.48,0:30:56.49,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,all the members stood firmly united in purpose.
Dialogue: 10,0:30:56.49,0:30:59.58,Narrator,,0,0,0,,For his own sake, for the happiness of the people,
Dialogue: 10,0:30:59.58,0:31:01.82,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and for the betterment of society,
Dialogue: 10,0:31:01.82,0:31:05.95,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Shinichi threw himself into spreading \Nthe Lotus Sutra and uplifting the members.
Dialogue: 10,0:31:10.35,0:31:13.35,Narrator,,0,0,0,,With Yamamoto Shinichi at its center,
Dialogue: 10,0:31:13.35,0:31:19.74,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Soka Gakkai made greater strides than ever before and continued to expand in all directions.
Dialogue: 10,0:31:20.96,0:31:29.66,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Then finally, two years after Toda's death, \Nhe was ushered in as the next president.
Dialogue: 10,0:31:43.49,0:31:49.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Although I'm still young, from today on I will represent all of Toda's disciples
Dialogue: 10,0:31:49.23,0:31:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and take the lead in taking the Common Path \Nto the next, global stage!
Dialogue: 10,0:32:08.20,0:32:10.74,Top,,0,0,0,,Have a safe trip! {itterashai}
Dialogue: 10,0:32:10.74,0:32:13.00,Top,,0,0,0,,Take care!
Dialogue: 10,0:32:13.39,0:32:14.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Good luck!
Dialogue: 10,0:32:14.75,0:32:16.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Hang in there! 
Dialogue: 10,0:32:19.00,0:32:23.38,Thought,,0,0,0,,Sensei, I'm off. Goodbye! {/I'll be going now}
Dialogue: 10,0:32:23.71,0:32:26.34,Narrator,,0,0,0,,With his journey to America,
Dialogue: 10,0:32:26.34,0:32:31.38,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Yamamoto Shinichi at last took his first step \Ntoward globalizing the Common Path. {/first step in the journey of the global CP}
Dialogue: 10,0:32:31.93,0:32:36.68,Narrator,,0,0,0,,To fulfill the lifelong dream of his mentor, Toda Josei,
Dialogue: 10,0:32:36.68,0:32:42.57,Narrator,,0,0,0,,who wholeheartedly yearned for peace \Nand happiness for all people around the world.
